caption: training and nutrition aesthetic v performance   some of the difference include  <Number>  calorie requirement may be different  performance goal usually require maintenance calorie or even a surplus depending on how active you are  aesthetic goal usually require being in a calorie deficit    <Number>  training look different  training for aesthetic is usually some bodybuilding format with some form of light cardio  training for performance is usually sport specific like pitch training  strength session or even high volume session like crossfit    <Number>  nutrient profile may be different  firstly  weight loss requires you to be in a calorific deficit  technically  you could eat <Number> mar bar a day and lose weight  i wouldnt recommend it  but youd achieve your goal  where a if you tried to perform at your best for a sport on <Number> mar bar a day  i can not imagine youd be performing very well  nutrition for aesthetic can be a simple a calorie in versus calorie out  nutrition for performance is much more intricate  do you have enough fuel  are you recovering ok  do you have a full nutrient profile  are you consuming good fat for hormonal balance and recovery    these are some of the main difference in nutrition and training when you have different goal  can you think of more  ğŸ¤” ğŸ“¸ <Handle>

caption: a you can see from my feed i have began to love crossfit ğŸ’‹   i didnt always love it and actually i wa a huge skeptic  my friend know this a some of them have questioned me on it ğŸ¤” but my view and opinion on so many thing over the year have changed  i also believed that a restrictive clean  diet wa the healthiest diet there could be  forgetting the impact that restriction ha on your mental health ğŸ¤·â€â™€ï¸ğŸ¤·â€â™€ï¸   i have made so many mistake over the year ive been in the health and fitness industry  ive called food good  and bad   and ive shunned certain exercise routine  but from experience come knowledge and wisdom  ğŸ™ and i am a lot more open minded to thing now ğŸ‘Œ   i dont think crossfit is for everyone  it a seriously stringent training regime which requires a huge level of mobility  strength and conditioning  even at a regressed level  it can be overwhelming and injury level can be high due to poor training technique or poor coaching  this is obviously not all coach   but i also dont think everyone should be running  poor running technique can contribute to any number of problem with joint  ligament  tendon or muscle strain    i am a firm believer in anyone starting out on a fitness journey  to look around  find what work for you  there not a one size fit all  i would normally say to get a coach to steer you in the right direction and then youll find a lifestyle you can enjoy â¤ï¸ because exercise should not be a punishment ğŸ™ #fitliving #ineedtopostthiscauseiwontbetrainingforawhile #fitlifestyle #fitlife #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitfam #irishfitfam

what is iron and why is it important    iron is an essential mineral needed by the body  it primary function is to transport oxygen in the haemoglobin of red blood cell so the cell can produce energy  it also help to remove carbon   how much iron do you need and where do we get it    infant and toddler need more iron than adult because their body are still growing  woman need more iron than men due to menstruation  woman require about  while men need just   iron is found in food like  shellfish  liver  red meat  spinach  kale and fortified cereal  haem iron is the iron we get from animal source and is most easily absorbed in the body  non haem iron come from plant source and is not a easily absorbed so may require supplementation in vegetarian and vegan  vitamin c is also essential for iron absorption  it â€™ s found in many fruit like blackcurrants  strawberry  kiwi and orange  adding orange juice or fruit to an iron rich meal can help absorption    how do i know if i â€™ m deficient in iron    common symptom of iron deficiency anaemia include  fatigue  paleness  difficulty exercising  or have a fast heartbeat  it is important to never self diagnose  too much iron is toxic and should not be taken unless recommended by a medical professional    female athlete are at risk of iron deficiency anaemia due to menstruation and high exercise output  make sure if you are showing any of the symptom to get it checked out by a doctor and never self diagnose  #irondeficiency #anaemia #healthylifestyle #healthyliving #athlete #fitliving #fitlife #fitlifestyle #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption: one of the most common question i get asked is about a pre match meal  well let me tell you  pre match fuel begin long before the pre match meal  ğŸ˜ƒ   a discussed in previous post  carbohydrate are the main fuel source involved in gaa  we can store <Number> <Number> in our liver and <Number> <Number> in our muscle a glycogen  but a glucose is constantly being used a a fuel source it is constantly depleting therefore we need to top it up regularly    pre match nutriton begin the day before a game  so if you play sunday at <Number>  you should be topping glycogen store from <Number> saturday  i recommend a carbohydrate source with each meal like cous cous for lunch  potato for dinner and oat for breakfast the following morning  closer to game time  fruit is a great source of caÌrbohydrate  protein is also essential  a athlete we are constantly in recovery mode for our next session so protein need to be a part of our pre match routine  although it wont be used a fuel it is an important element for muscle repair etc    some donts the day of a game âŒâŒâŒ â high fat food are harder to break down in the body and may cause gastrointestinal upset so best to avoid large quantity of fat  save them for afterwards when we need to reduce inflammation â high fibre food can also cause gastrointestinal issue and while fibre is a vital part of a healthy diet  it best to avoid large quantity before game â strong flavoured food   some do âœ”ï¸âœ”ï¸âœ”ï¸ â˜‘ï¸ nutrient dense food with a caÌrbohydrate and protein element ğŸ‘‰oats with whey protein  egg and toast  fruit salad with greek yogurt  chicken and pasta  fish and potato â˜‘ï¸ dont forget about water  hydration is a key pre match ritual hope this help ğŸ˜ƒ never change a routine the day of a game  slowly make change in the day leading up to a game ğŸ‘Œ #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitlife #prematch #nutrition #fitliving #fitfam #irishfitfam
